<b>Subject:</b> Re: About monks<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=863" TARGET=_self>About monks</A> (Ainulindale)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I've got a level 4 monk right now, they have an ability called mend which, with a lot of training on your part, will completely heal you (as far as I've seen). This skill can only be used pretty rarely though, so is only to be used when needed. Monks also get a large variety of supplemental attacks, things like kicks. My monk has been able to dish out more damage quicker than a warrior of the same level. Add to this skills like dodge and block and you've got one great fighter. They are very self-sufficient, I don't care too much about dying because even if I can't get back to my corpse, money is pretty much useless to me right now. Monks don't need weapons, armor, or spells. I love it.

<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
